    <discussion>Fimbristylis miliacea is another widespread annual weed whose origin is probably in
        the Asian rice belt. Two Linnaean types bear the epithet “miliacea.” A good argument exists
        that Vahl, first to adopt the plant as a Fimbristylis, took the round-spikeleted element as
        F. miliacea; the other, ovoid, acute-spikeleted element thus became F. quinquangularis
        (Vahl) Kunth.</discussion>
    <discussion>Because Gaudichaud’s epithet “littoralis” was not applied to the complex until 1826,
